RATIONALE:
Based on the system description and technical constraints provided by the Customer, I have identified three primary architectural approaches. 1) An ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) / Batch Processing pattern is necessary to synchronize data from disparate legacy PHP/MySQL applications without requiring invasive modifications to them. 2) A Centralized Repository style is used to consolidate academic records into a single source of truth for accreditation. 3) A File Mirroring and Synchronization service is identified to handle the specific technical constraint where binary media files are stored on server hard drives rather than in the databases. These approaches align with the identified quality attribute drivers (Security, Performance, Compliance, Modifiability) while respecting the constraints of low-cost, open-source software and limited development expertise.
